<DOCNO> AP890826-0011 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-08-26-89 0053EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a PM-Names     08-26 0863</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Names,0902</SECOND>
<HEAD>Names in the News</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor Martin Sheen took his crusade to help
the homeless to Hollywood's Walk of Fame while accepting a star in
his honor there.
   ``The sidewalks of Hollywood are known all over the world as the
Walk of Fame, but many sidewalks in America could be known a the
`Walk of Shame' because of the 4 million homeless people residing on
them full time,'' Sheen said Friday.
   In his role as honorary mayor of Malibu, the 49-year-old Sheen
recently declared the wealthy beach community a sanctuary for the
homeless.
   The actor, flanked by his wife, Janet, and sons Emilio Estevez
and Charlie Sheen, asked the crowd to pray with him for 400,000
homeless children.
   Sheen made his New York stage debut in 1959 in ``The Connection''
and his movies include ``Apocalypse Now,'' and ``Wall Street.'' He
was the 1,897th recipient of the Hollywood star.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lech Walesa, who has led the Solidarity
movement to form the first non-Communist government in Poland since
just after World War II, forgot to tell his son his new telephone
number.
   Lech's 17-year-old son, Slawek, who has been touring the United
States with a polka band for two months, tried to call his father
Thursday but found the number no longer functioned because of
changes in the Polish phone service.
   Slawek Walesa said he didn't have his father's new number.
   The younger Walesa, who is returning to Gdansk on Monday to
finish his last year of high school, said he thought his father
would be more effective heading Solidarity than being prime minister.
   Tadeusz Mazoviecki, a longtime Solidarity activist, was selected
by Walesa to head the government and was elected by the assembly as
prime minister Thursday.
   Walesa has said he preferred to remain as Solidarity's chief
rather than taking the reins of government.
