<HEAD>Hotel Fire Kills Seven, Injures 17</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto PAR1</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire broke out in the stairwell of a suburban
hotel and spread through the top floor of the four-story building,
killing seven guests and injuring 17, police said Saturday.
   Three people burned to death and four fell to their deaths after
jumping out of windows to escape the flames, a fire department
official said.
   Four guests of the Hotel Hennouf Gouta de Clichy in the northwest
suburb of Clichy were seriously burned and taken to a nearby
hospital, the official said. Thirteen others suffered minor smoke
inhalation, the official said on condition of anonymity.
